# HTML PR Review

Use this checklist when reviewing pull requests that modify HTML files.

## Structure and Semantics

- **Document type**: Does the file start with `<!doctype html>`?
- **Language**: Is `lang` set on `<html>` (e.g. `lang="en"`)?
- **Semantic elements**: Use `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>` instead of generic `<div>` where appropriate.
- **Heading hierarchy**: Are headings in logical order (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`) with no skipped levels?
- **Single h1**: One `<h1>` per page for the primary topic.

## Head and Meta

- **Charset**: `<meta charset="utf-8" />` present in `<head>`.
- **Viewport**: `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />` for responsive layouts.
- **Title**: Descriptive, unique `<title>` per page.
- **Description**: `<meta name="description" content="...">` for SEO (50–160 chars).
- **Robots**: `index,follow` or `noindex` as intended for the page.

## Accessibility

- **Images**: All `<img>` have meaningful `alt` attributes (or `alt=""` for decorative images).
- **Links**: Link text is descriptive; avoid "click here" or raw URLs.
- **External links**: Use `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"` when opening in a new tab.
- **Form labels**: Every form control has an associated `<label>`.
- **Focus**: Interactive elements are keyboard-focusable; no `tabindex="-1"` on primary actions unless justified.
- **ARIA**: Use ARIA only when semantic HTML is insufficient; prefer native elements.

## Links and Navigation

- **Anchor targets**: `href="#id"` targets exist and match section `id` attributes.
- **Mailto links**: `mailto:` links have sensible `subject` and optional `body` prefill.
- **Broken links**: No dead links or placeholder `#` hrefs.

## Security

- **XSS**: No `innerHTML`, `eval()`, `document.write()`, or `javascript:` URLs with user-controlled or dynamic content. Use `textContent` or safe DOM APIs.
- **External links**: Use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` on all `target="_blank"` links to prevent `window.opener` access.
- **javascript: URLs**: No `href="javascript:..."` — use `<button>` or proper event handlers instead.
- **Form actions**: Forms must submit to `https://` URLs, never `http://` for sensitive data.
- **No secrets**: No API keys, tokens, passwords, or credentials in HTML, attributes, or inline scripts.
- **External scripts/styles**: Prefer SRI (`integrity` + `crossorigin`) when loading from CDNs. Use `crossorigin="anonymous"` for CORS.
- **Data attributes**: No sensitive data in `data-*` attributes that could be exposed to client-side scripts.
- **Form autocomplete**: Use `autocomplete="off"` on sensitive fields only when necessary; avoid on login/payment forms unless explicitly required.

## Performance

- **Script placement**: Non-critical scripts at end of `<body>` or use `defer`/`async` where appropriate.

## Responsiveness

- **Media queries**: Layout adapts for mobile, tablet, and desktop.
- **Touch targets**: Buttons and links are at least 44×44px for touch.
- **Readable text**: No horizontal scrolling; font sizes scale reasonably.

## Style and Consistency

- **Inline vs. external**: Inline styles are acceptable for single-page sites; consider external CSS if reused.
- **CSS variables**: Use `:root` variables for colors, spacing, and typography where it improves maintainability.
- **Print**: Consider `@media print` if the page is likely to be printed.

## Examples

### Semantic structure

```html
<!-- Prefer semantic elements -->
<header>...</header>
<main>
  <section id="services">...</section>
  <section id="contact">...</section>
</main>
<footer>...</footer>
```

### External links

```html
<!-- Always use rel="noopener noreferrer" for target="_blank" -->
<a href="https://example.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Example</a>
```

### Accessible images

```html
<!-- Meaningful alt for content images -->
<img src="diagram.png" alt="Architecture diagram showing EKS cluster layout" />

<!-- Empty alt for decorative images -->
<img src="decoration.svg" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
```

### Security: safe script usage

```html
<!-- BAD: XSS risk with user content -->
<script>document.getElementById("x").innerHTML = userInput;</script>

<!-- GOOD: Safe text insertion -->
<script>document.getElementById("x").textContent = userInput;</script>
```

### Security: external script with SRI

```html
<!-- Prefer SRI when loading from CDN -->
<script src="https://cdn.example.com/lib.js"
        integrity="sha384-..."
        crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
```

### Security: avoid javascript: URLs

```html
<!-- BAD -->
<a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="doThing()">Click</a>

<!-- GOOD -->
<button type="button" onclick="doThing()">Click</button>
```
